om the drawing, appear deeply cut letters without marked serifs, of a slightly irregular module. Alpha with straight bar; M with vertical outer strokes and all full length; omicron nearly full size; omega closed and rhomboid. Line 1 appears to be clearly bigger than lines 2-4. (measurements taken from the drawing)",[63,69,74],{"type":64,"l":65,"from":66,"to":66,"h":67,"unit":68},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","20","mm",{"type":64,"l":70,"from":71,"to":72,"h":73,"unit":68},"Line 2-4","line2","line4","12-15",{"type":75,"l":76,"from":66,"to":71,"unit":68},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2",{"_":78,"notBefore":79,"notAfter":80,"evidence":81},"Later 2nd or 1st century BCE",-150,-1,"lettering",[83,88],{"_":84,"type":85,"ref":86,"region":87},"Syracusae","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462503","Sicilia",{"_":89,"type":90,"ref":91,"region":87},"Siracusa","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2523083",[93],[94,95],37.08415,15.27628,{"_":97,"type":98,"subtype":99,"geo":21},"From among the sporadic finds in the clearing of modern structures from the area of the Apollonion in Ortygia, undertaken between 1938 and 1948.","found","discovered",[],{"_":102,"type":103,"subtype":104,"geo":21},"None","observed","autopsied",{"_":106,"type":107,"subtype":108,"geo":21},"Neither Manganaro, nor the I.Sicily project have so far been able to locate the fragment in the museum stores, and so the only direct evidence is the drawing of Cultrera","not-observed","lost",[110],{"n":111,"url":112,"height":113,"width":114,"desc":115,"surfaceType":116},"screen","ISic003174_tiled.tif","769px","943px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana: drawing of Cultrera, MAL 1951: 811 fig.87","front","Sicily",{"_":119,"role":120,"ref":121,"museum":122},"Museo Archeologico Regionale Paolo Orsi","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/097",{"slug":123,"type":120,"name":119,"uri":121,"description":124,"location":125},"097","An outstanding collection of archaeological material. The collection ranges from Siracusa and the surrounding territory (Megara Hyblaia, Akrai, Kasmenai etc) to encompass all of eastern Sicily, reaching as far as Gela and Agrigento. The ground floor covers prehistory through to the end of the Classical period. Upstairs includes Hellenistic and Roman Syracuse and a display of material from the catacombs. A gallery displaying material from Hellenistic eastern Sicily is in preparation.",{"settlement":89,"region":89,"country":126,"address":127,"geo":128},"Italy","Viale Teocrito 66, 96100 - Siracusa",{"lat":129,"lon":130},37.07636989,15.2866213,{"_":132,"mainLang":133,"languages":134},"Ancient Greek","grc",[132],{"type":136,"bibl":137},"edition",[138,150,153,165,176,187],{"type":139,"n":140,"citedRange":141,"ptr":142,"ref":143,"title":144,"author":145,"date":146,"citation":147,"uri":148,"year":149},"bulletin","SEG","49.1331.2",{"target":143},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F2GG87EQ","Supplementum epigraphicum graecum","","1923-","\u003Cspan>‘Supplementum Epigraphicum Graecum’, \u003Ci>Supplementum Epigraphicum Graecum\u003C/i>, 1923, \u003Ca href=\"http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1607583\">http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1607583\u003C/a>\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/F2GG87EQ","1923",{"type":139,"n":140,"citedRange":151,"ptr":152,"ref":143,"title":144,"author":145,"date":146,"citation":147,"uri":148,"year":149},"14.0580",{"target":143},{"type":139,"n":154,"citedRange":155,"ptr":156,"ref":158,"title":160,"author":145,"date":161,"citation":162,"uri":163,"year":164},"BE","1953.0281",{"target":157},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/77P5MNIR",{"_":159,"target":159},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282","Bulletin épigraphique","1888-","\u003Cspan>Association pour l’encouragement des études greques, « Bulletin épigraphique », \u003Ci>Revue des études grecques\u003C/i>, 18